00020 MasterInterface::MasterInterface(QDomNode& masterNode): addressSpaceRef_(),
00021 baseAddress_(), prompt_(QString("Base Address:")), baseAttributes_() {
00022 
00023         // go through all child items
00024         for (int i = 0; i < masterNode.childNodes().count(); ++i) {
00025                 QDomNode tempNode = masterNode.childNodes().at(i);
00026 
00027                 if (tempNode.nodeName() == QString("spirit:addressSpaceRef")) {
00028                         // get the addressSpaceRef attribute
00029                         QDomNamedNodeMap attributeMap = tempNode.attributes();
00030                         addressSpaceRef_ = attributeMap.namedItem(QString(
00031                                         "spirit:addressSpaceRef")).nodeValue();
00032                         addressSpaceRef_ = General::removeWhiteSpace(addressSpaceRef_);
00033 
00034                         // search the baseAddress element
00035                         for (int j = 0; j < tempNode.childNodes().count(); ++j) {
00036                                 if (tempNode.childNodes().at(j).nodeName() == QString(
00037                                                 "spirit:baseAddress")) {
00038                                         tempNode = tempNode.childNodes().at(j);
00039                                         baseAddress_ = tempNode.childNodes().at(0).nodeValue();
00040                                         baseAddress_ = General::removeWhiteSpace(baseAddress_);
00041                                         break;
00042                                 }
00043                         }
00044                         // get the base address attributes
00045                         General::parseAttributes(tempNode, baseAttributes_);
00046 
00047                         // if contains the optional attribute prompt then set the
00048                         // prompt value in prompt_ and remove the attribute from the
00049                         // QMap to avoid duplicate data
00050                         QMap<QString, QString>::iterator i = baseAttributes_.find(
00051                                         QString("spirit:prompt"));
00052                         if (i != baseAttributes_.end()) {
00053 
00054                                 // save the prompt value
00055                                 prompt_ = i.value();
00056 
00057                                 // remove from map
00058                                 baseAttributes_.erase(i);
00059                         }
00060 
00061                         // if mandatory attribute addressSpaceRef is missing
00062                         if (addressSpaceRef_.isNull()) {
00063                                 throw Parse_error(QObject::tr("Mandatory attribute spirit:"
00064                                                 "addressSpaceRef is missing in spirit:addressSpaceRef"
00065                                 ));
00066                         }
00067                 }
00068         }
00069         return;
00070 }

00101 void MasterInterface::write(QXmlStreamWriter& writer) {
00102         // spirit:master can't be written here because this class is used also
00103         // in spirit:mirroredMaster. The writing has to be done in previous level
00104 
00105         // if nothing is to be written just return and dont write the opening
00106         // tag
00107         if (addressSpaceRef_.isEmpty())
00108                 return;
00109         
00110 
00111         writer.writeStartElement("spirit:addressSpaceRef");
00112         writer.writeAttribute("spirit:addressSpaceRef", addressSpaceRef_);
00113 
00114         // if optional element baseAddress is not empty
00115         if (!baseAddress_.isEmpty()) {
00116                 // start the spirit:baseAddress tag
00117                 writer.writeStartElement("spirit:baseAddress");
00118 
00119                 // if prompt attribute is defined
00120                 if (!prompt_.isEmpty()) {
00121                         writer.writeAttribute("spirit:prompt", prompt_);
00122                 }
00123                 // write rest of the attributes
00124                 General::writeAttributes(writer, baseAttributes_);
00125 
00126                 // write the value of the baseAddress element and close the tag
00127                 writer.writeCharacters(baseAddress_);
00128                 writer.writeEndElement(); // spirit:baseAddress
00129         }
00130 
00131         writer.writeEndElement(); // spirit:addressSpaceRef
00132         return;
00133 }
